player.seasonOutlook: After spending much of his first few NBA seasons coming off the bench, Brunson started for the Mavericks last season and showed he could be a secondary offensive engine next to a mega-usage player like Luka Doncic. However, when Doncic missed time, Brunson gave glimpses of his upside as the primary creator. During a 10-game Doncic absence in December, Brunson averaged 21.0 PPG (51.3 FG%, 37.5 3P%, 77.5 FT%), 7.4 APG, 3.5 RPG and 1.5 3PG in 34.7 MPG. When Doncic missed the first three games of the playoffs. Brunson responded by averaging 32.0 PPG (50.7 FG%, 41.2 3P%, 85.0 FT%), 5.3 APG, 5.3 RPG and 2.3 3PG in 39.4 MPG. In New York, Brunson should get the keys to the franchise, and put up strong individual numbers while putting his teammates in better positions for them to thrive as well.
